Comment.MultiLanguageText: Set once MU spin torq above setpoint
Latch that will allow Drill rev if rotary has stopped

AttributeList.Text: Written BY Kristopher Gimenez Feb1,2023 This block is used to control the TD control mode, pump outputs and HSLT/LSHT shifting
Determine Control Mode based on Console Inputs and interlocks.
Control Mode
Allow shift change if throttle zero and TD stopped
Shift Enable
Allow Shifting. Bypass in HSLT. MU modes, BO and Osc in LSHT. Drill modes follow console input
HSLT/LSHT
Set throttle unlock if Console enabled and Drill throttle less than min. . Bit will be reset by other functions that will lock throttle requiring throttle to be zero'd before being enabled again
Drill Throttle Unlock
Disable throttle if Bypass, Throttle disabled due to shift, or Flush fault or if throttle not unlocked
Drill Throttle Disable
Reset local control variables. All values to be set by mode enabled
Reset Local Output variables
In Drill Mode, Torq Pot command is always sent to Torq valve. Throttle command to both Forward pumps if throttle not disabled and Throttle Above setpoint.
Drill
Only allow reverse if TD has stopped moving forward and Throttle above zero. No torq control in reverse. Set at relief
Drill Reverse
Output if Throttle not disabled after a shift, flush not disabled, Drill Throttle Input Zero
Make Up Spin
Output if Throttle not disabled after a shift, flush not disabled, Drill Throttle Input Zero
Make Up Torque
Output if Throttle not disabled after a shift, flush not disabled, Drill Throttle Input Zero. No torq control in reverse. Set at relief
Break Out
Oscillator

In Bypass Mode If gripper closed turn on Bypass valve(Quill is Locked after PTO funtioned) After PTO wait 8 seconds for system to enage before enabling bypass control outputs Note TD in HSLT in Bypass mode Bypass Running flag will stay on for Set time after Bypass mode finished
Bypass Mode

Limit Output to Pump if speed above Max Speed Low Setpoint While Limiting, Destroke Output to pump if above Max Speed High Setpoint and increase if below Note In HSLT, drill mode active and both pumps used
Max Speed Limiter

Limit Flow mA Output if High Temp reduced RPM.
Disable outputs 10 seconds after a shutdown and disable Throttle
High Temp Speed Limiter
Assign Local Variable to System Outputs
TD_Control
